HEADWORD: Fundament
<hw>Fun"da*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>fundament</ets>, <ets>fundement</ets>, <ets>fondement</ets>, OF.
<ets>fundement</ets>, <ets>fondement</ets>, F. <ets>fondement</ets>, fr.
L. <ets>fundamentum</ets> foundation, fr. <ets>fundare</ets> to lay the
bottom, to found, fr. <ets>fundus</ets> bottom. See
<er>Fund</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Foundation.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The part of the body on which one sits; the
buttocks; specifically <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, the anus.</def>
<rj><au>Hume.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fundamental</ent>⟦br⟧
